Investors should consider carefully the investment objectives, risks, and charges and expenses of a Fund before investing. The Funds' Prospectus contains this and other information about the Funds.

(1)  Weitz Investment Management, Inc., the  investment adviser, has agreed in writing to limit the total annual operating expenses of the Fund’s Institutional and Investor Class shares (in each case, excluding taxes, interest, brokerage costs, acquired fund fees and expenses and extraordinary expenses) to 0.99% and 1.30%, respectively, of the each Class's average daily net assets through July 31, 2017.    
    
(2) The investment adviser has agreed in writing to waive its fees and
reimburse certain expenses (excluding taxes, interest, brokerage costs,
acquired fund fees and expenses and extraordinary expenses) to limit the total
annual fund operating expenses for Institutional Class shares and Investor
Class shares to 0.48% and 0.68%, respectively, of each Class’ average daily net
assets through July 31, 2018.

(3) The investment adviser has agreed in writing to waive its fees and
reimburse certain expenses (excluding taxes, interest, brokerage costs,
acquired fund fees and expenses and extraordinary expenses) to limit the total
annual fund operating expenses for Institutional Class shares and Investor
Class shares to 0.40% and 0.60%, respectively, of each Class’s average daily
net assets through July 31, 2018.

(4) The investment advisor has agreed in writing to limit the total annual
fund operating expenses (excluding taxes, interest, brokerage costs, acquired
fund fees and expenses and extraordinary expenses) to 0.20% of the Institutional
Class shares’ average daily net assets through July 31, 2018. 




